On Escalation Ticket # 00437901 the new comment has been added: Hi, customer uploaded logs from 24th of March, job is being run as scheduled task, they do not abort it.

However I can see this messages in log:

"25/03/2025 18:00:40	INFO	StealthAUDIT	TJobQueueThread.RunNextJob	"Abort requested, clearing queue"		1-SPSEEK_SystemScans	5740	6616	11796
25/03/2025 18:00:40	INFO	StealthAUDIT	TJobQueueThread.RunNextJob	"Terminating normally"		1-SPSEEK_SystemScans	5740	6616	11796"

Sensitive data logs have this error:

"2025-03-24 12:26:12.6956|ERROR| 10|DLPScanner.Patterns.PatternMatcher|Error on initializing pattern Regex: PCRE2CS.RegexException: Failed to compile regexp {bCriminalb), error:  at position 13
   at PCRE2CS.Regex.Compile(String expression, RegexOption options)
   at PCRE2CS.Regex..ctor(String expression, RegexOption options)
   at DLPScanner.Patterns.Pcre2RegexPattern..ctor(RegExDefinition def, Guid id, Int64 numMatches, Int32 confidence, DataSources searchIn)
   at DLPScanner.Patterns.RegexPatternFactory.CreateRegexPattern(RegExDefinition def, Guid id, Int64 numMatches, Int32 confidence, DataSources searchIn, String engine, Boolean patternIsKeyword)
   at DLPScanner.Patterns.PatternMatcher.InitializePatterns(Boolean disableCharacterDistance)"

Which I am not sure if related.

Logs are uploaded to SP, please check.
On Escalation Ticket # 00437901 the new comment has been added: Hi, any updates for this issue?

On Escalation Ticket # 00437901 the new comment has been added: Hi, customer provided additional feedback, they've disabled EPP but scan still takes alot of time and it looks like it's being aborted. I've pointed out to customer that this job abortion might be caused by 3rd party tool. 

But disabling EPP didn't change anything, is there anything else to check?

On Escalation Ticket # 00437901 the new comment has been added: We've agreed with customer to have NEA installed on another box to exclude issues with this server, since job interruption seems like something is affecting NEA job from outside, and because after reviewing Windows events log I found some issues with disk, so I would like to confirm that server itself is not the issue.

I've collected Windows events logs and uploaded them to Sharepoint, please review and let me know if there's anything else you'll need for investigation.

On Escalation Ticket # 00437901 the new comment has been added: Adam DeSapio:

@Salesforce @WaitingOnEngineer

Still waiting on artifacts requested to further investigate issue. 

As a possible workaround they could try checking "Limit maximum number of Probable Owners per resource" and set a reasonable value in the checkbox. 
This setting is found in the SPAA DC wizard. If scans finish in a reasonable amount of time, that would tell us if the Probable Owners calculation is causing the large delay after the scan finishes but before the job finishes

On Escalation Ticket # 00437901 the new comment has been added: Hi Chris, customer confirmed that the issue is not occurring on server that is outside of DMZ, server outside of DMZ finishes scan in 13 minutes, customer however asked for assistance in determining the root cause, I've requested packet capture from both servers.

Looks like an infrastructure issue to me, but if we can point them in the right direction, it would be something they can work with.

Waiting on customer to provide packet capture.

On Escalation Ticket # 00437901 the new comment has been added: Hi Chris, customer asked to increase priority on this case, I suspected that packet capture can help to determine the issue, but may I ask you to confirm this with development?

Customer is asking for a meeting to compare both servers, but I am not sure which area should I investigate on those servers, since required ports were checked previously.

To my understanding, we need to trace the connection to SPO and see if we're hitting any bumps.

Is it worth having a call with a developer to troubleshoot the issue at this point?
On Escalation Ticket # 00437901 the new comment has been added: Hi, customer provided packet capture, please check and advise on further steps for customer.

On Escalation Ticket # 00437901 the new comment has been added: Hi, any update on this one? Customer applied the same FW rules for both servers, but they still can see the issue with server that is inside of DMZ.

They've scheduled a call on Monday, could you please advise what metrics/details should I look for aside of standard ports 80 and 443?

On Escalation Ticket # 00437901 the new comment has been added: Customer provided more tests results from another server, that they moved into DMZ:

"We changed the POC server ip and moved it to the same subnet  as the DMZ server.

 

The scan runs just as fast as it did previously , however our 2nd test scan got stuck at some point and we found that it was stuck in what looks like a loop where it was “checkpointing” , we stop the scan and ran it again , it continued from where it stopped and finished of in 7 minutes.

 

We than ran a 3rd test scan and it finished in 8 minutes."


I suggest reviewing this issue with developer on call if that's possible, it's an urgent issue for customer.
